/bin (Essential Binaries): Contains fundamental commands for all users (e.g., ls, cd, sh) required during system boot or repair.
/sbin (System Binaries): Contains essential system management/administration binaries, typically used by the root user (e.g., fsck, ifconfig).
/usr/bin (User Binaries): Holds the majority of executable commands available to regular users, such as editors (vi), interpreters (python), and tools.
/usr/sbin (Non-essential System Binaries): Holds system administration binaries that are not strictly necessary for basic booting or repair

