7.Using Jenkins, how would you design and implement a fully automated Continuous Deployment?
Every successful commit to the main (or release) branch that passes all automated checks is automatically deployed to production without a manual approval gate.
Safety is preserved by progressive delivery (canary/blue‑green), health/metrics gates, and automatic rollback.
Core components:
SCM: GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket (webhook → Jenkins)
Jenkins: Multibranch Pipeline + agents (static or Kubernetes auto‑scaled)
Build Tool: Maven/Gradle/npm/etc.
Artifact Repo: Artifactory/Nexus or container registry (ECR/GCR/ACR/Docker Hub)
Security/Quality Gates: SonarQube, SCA (e.g., OWASP Dependency‑Check, Snyk), image scanner (Trivy/Anchore)
