Capabilities of a Splunk User
Can run searches in allowed indexes
Can view dashboards, reports, and alerts
Can use existing knowledge objects (saved searches, macros, lookups, etc.)
Can export search results
Can use time pickers and filters
Limited ability to edit or create dashboards (depending on role settings)

Capabilities of a Splunk Power User
In addition to everything a Splunk User can do, a Power User can:
✔ Create and edit knowledge objects
Tags
Field extractions (regex-based)
Lookups (creating & editing)
Data model acceleration
Workflow actions
Search macros
Calculated/automatic fields

✔ Create & manage dashboards and reports
Create dashboards shared at app level
Create scheduled searches
Manage alert permissions

✔ More powerful search capabilities
Use advanced commands (summaries, pivots, data models)
Accelerate data models to speed up dashboards
Create summary indexes

